summary: This Apache module exports an optional function named TestOptionalFn that can be imported by other modules. It serves as a demonstration of the optional function registration system in Apache HTTP Server, allowing modules to access functions from other modules without creating hard dependencies.

logs.reason: Logs a debug message when the TestOptionalFn function is called, including the string parameter passed to the function. This is likely used for debugging and tracing when the optional function is being used by other modules.
logs.resolution: This is an informational debug log message and doesn't require resolution. If seen in logs, it indicates that the TestOptionalFn function was called successfully by another module.
